WINDOW VS SCREEN VS DOCUMENT:

What is the difference between window, screen, and document in Javascript?

Window is the global object.once the browser is loaded window is the first thing that will get initialized. and Window holds the property of Screen and document. i.e. window.screen, window.document

Screen has the details about individuals screen property such as  width, height of the browser's screen.

Document is the root of the DOM Tree. if we want to access any nodes in DOM tree then, (Document.getElementById) can be used to access the DOM tree.
